"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 28 "Do the rest from 1 to 10.   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 31 "Note:  it is possible to use a " }{TEXT 263 9 "for loop \+
" }{TEXT -1 69 " to simplify this task since we are doing a repetitive
 calculation.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "Note:  Also, the the c
ommand " }{TEXT 265 6 "coeffs" }{TEXT -1 15 " unfortunately " }{TEXT 
266 8 "does not" }{TEXT -1 36 " pick off the coefficients in order." }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }
{TEXT 259 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for fin
ding the coefficients of the expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" 
"6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 267 1 
"n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is relatively obvious that the coefficient of \+
 " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^(n-k)*b^k;" "6#*&)%\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!\"\"F()
%\"bGF)F(" }{TEXT -1 19 "  for any value of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" }{TEXT 
-1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 269 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the nu
mber of ways we can choose " }{TEXT 270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }
{TEXT 294 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT 
-1 1 " " }{TEXT 295 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }
{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }
{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The numbe
r of combinations of " }{TEXT 273 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosin
g " }{TEXT 274 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 " at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "C(n,k
);" "6#-%\"CG6$%\"nG%\"kG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is given by the formula  " 
}{XPPEDIT 18 0 "C(n,k) = n!/(k!*(n-k)!);" "6#/-%\"CG6$%\"nG%\"kG*&-%*f
actorialG6#F'\"\"\"*&-F+6#F(F--F+6#,&F'F-F(!\"\"F-F4" }{TEXT -1 2 " .
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 261 10 "Stat
e the " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 275 
31 "and use Maple to demonstrate it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 107 "=C(n,0)a^n*b^0+C(n.1)a^(n-1)*b^1+C(n,2)a^(n-2)*b
^2+...+C(n,n-2)a^2*b(n-2)+C(n,n-1)a^1*b(n-1)+C(n,n)a^0*b^n." }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "expand((a+b)^9);" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,6*$)%\"aG\"\"*\"\"\"F(*(F'F()F&\"\")F(%\"bG
F(F(*(\"#OF()F&\"\"(F()F,\"\"#F(F(*(\"#%)F()F&\"\"'F()F,\"\"$F(F(*(\"$
E\"F()F&\"\"&F()F,\"\"%F(F(*(F:F()F&F>F()F,F<F(F(*(F4F()F&F8F()F,F6F(F
(*(F.F()F&F2F()F,F0F(F(*(F'F(F&F()F,F+F(F(*$)F,F'F(F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 8 "Compute " }{XPPEDIT 
18 0 "sum(binomial(n,k),k=0..n)" "6#-%$sumG6$-%)binomialG6$%\"nG%\"kG/
F*;\"\"!F)" }{TEXT -1 34 "  for n=1 to 10.  Here the symbol " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "Sigma;" "6#%&SigmaG" }{TEXT -1 70 " (Greek letter Sigma
) stands for sum.   (See the worksheet SumSeq.mws)" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 60 "for i from 1 to 10\ndo\ni, sum(coeff((a+1)^i
,a,k),k=0..i);\nod;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"\"\"#" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"#\"\"%" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"$\"\")" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"%\"#;
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"&\"#K" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"'\"#k" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"(\"$G
\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\")\"$c#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"*\"$7&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"#5\"%C5
" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 258 59 "Wha
t general formula do the above calculations in  suggest?" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "Sum=2^i" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 172 "2.  Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the def
inition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use Maple to construct the first 10 ro
ws of Pascal's Triangle.  Hint:  Consider the coefficients of   " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+1)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"F&F&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 16 "   \+
rather than  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG
" }{TEXT -1 291 "  -- even though they are the same.  The trick will b
e to get the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  The Maple co
mmand for generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(expressi
on(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with index i and
 m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "   " }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 56 "for i from 0 to 9\ndo\nseq(c
oeff((a+1)^i,a,n),n=0..i);\nod;" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
