{TEXT -1 214 "3.  Functions.  In this exericse we study the basic prop
erties of polynomials and rational functions.  Some revelant Maple com
mands will be   factor, expand, solve, fsolve, denom, numer, simplify,
 subs,   ....... ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 171 "     The first thi
ng we need to learn is how to define a function.  There are two ways, \+
each with its own advantages and disadvantages.  First define the poly
nomial p1 as " }{TEXT 282 2 "a " }{TEXT -1 1 "s" }{TEXT 283 23 "ymboli
c expression in x" }{TEXT -1 119 " in the following way:    p1:=x^2-1;
  (Note the colon before the =, this is always required when defining \+
something.)  " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 " p1:=x^2-1;
 " }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p1G,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F*F*!
\"\"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 "
     Now define the same polynomial as " }{TEXT 281 30 "an operation o
n the variable x" }{TEXT -1 40 " in the following way:     p2:=x->x^2-
1;" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "p2:=x->x^2-1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p
2Gf*6#%\"xG6\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowGF(,&*$)9$\"\"#\"\"\"F1F1!\"\"F(F(F(
" }}}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 257 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 190 
"Try the following command sequences to see some of the differences in
 how Maple  treats these two definitions.  As always record your obser
vations and comments on the worksheet in text mode." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "p1;" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(!\"\"" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 107 "p1 is defined as x^2-1 and when p
1 is used as a symbolic expression  it is defined as x^2-1, xis a vari
able" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "p2;" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%#p2G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 134 "p2 \+
is an operation on the variable x it cannot define anything or in this
 case be anything, when p2 is entered Maple responds with p2 " }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
6 "p2(x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(
!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 48 "p2 as an operation that \+
substitutes x^2-1 for x," }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "
p2(t-3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$),&%\"tG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"
\"\"\"#F(F(F(F*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "with t-3 typed
 in p2 it replaces the x and gives this equation" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "p2(u^3-u^2+2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#,&*$),(*$)%\"uG\"\"$\"\"\"F+*$)F)\"\"#F+!\"\"F.F+F.F+F+F+F/" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 64 "as in the last equation this entir
e polynomial is inserted for x" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 255 "     This works just like we expect su
bstitution to work because p2 is an operation on whatever is in the ( \+
 ).  However since p1 is a symbolic expression we have some difficulti
es with substituting into it directly.   Try the following command seq
uences." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p1(x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)-%\"xG6
#F'\"\"#\"\"\"F*F*!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "p
1(t-3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)-%\"xG6#,&%\"tG\"\"\"
\"\"$!\"\"\"\"#F+F+F+F-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "
p1(u^3-u^2+2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)-%\"xG6#,(*$)%
\"uG\"\"$\"\"\"F.*$)F,\"\"#F.!\"\"F1F.F1F.F.F.F2" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 135 "      Notice the extra x
 in front.  This is curious and not very reassuring.  To substitute in
to a symbolic expression we must use the " }{TEXT 284 4 "subs" }{TEXT 
-1 9 " command." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "subs(x=t-3,p1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#,&*$),&%\"tG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"\"\"\"#F(F(F(F*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "subs(x=6,p1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 
"6#\"#N" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p2(6);" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"#N" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "    " }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 75 "     Now let's do some simple operations
 on this polynomial.  In each case " }{TEXT 277 46 "Explain what the c
ommand appears to have done." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "factor(p1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&!\"\"F&,&F%F&F&F&F&" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 32 "It factored the the equation p1." }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "factor(p2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%#p2G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 41 "p2 i
s an operation, it can't be factored." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
