0 "" {TEXT 278 91 "   Why did we need to include the ,x in the solve c
ommand in order to find the roots of p3?" }{TEXT -1 2 "  " }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 98 "There are four unknowns in the equation, \+
a, b, c, and x. It solves the equation in the terms of x." }}}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 107 "Use the solve co
mmand replacing x with a, b, c respectively.  You should be able to an
ticipate the results." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p3=0,a);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#,$*&,&*&%\"bG\"\"\"%\"xGF(F(%\"cGF(F(F)!\"#!\"\"" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p3=0,b);" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,$*&,&*&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"#F(F(%\"cGF(F(F*!\"
\"F-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p3=0,c);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"#F&!\"\"*&%\"
bGF&F(F&F*" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 2 "  " }{TEXT 279 58 "What's the famous formula we get when we solv
e p3=0 for x?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 "This is known as the qua
dratic formula." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 169 "  See if Maple knows a general formula for solving gener
al cubic polynomials, i.e. is there a 3rd order formula comparable to \+
the quadratic formula?  If so, exhibit it. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "p4:=a*x^3+b*x^2+c*
x+d;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p4G,**&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"
\"$F(F(*&%\"bGF()F*\"\"#F(F(*&%\"cGF(F*F(F(%\"dGF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p4=0,x);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6%,(*(\"\"'!\"\"%\"aGF&,***\"#O\"\"\"%\"bGF+%\"cGF+F'F+F+
*(\"$3\"F+%\"dGF+)F'\"\"#F+F&*&\"\")F+)F,\"\"$F+F&**\"#7F+F6#F+F2,,*(
\"\"%F+F'F+)F-F6F+F+*&)F-F2F+)F,F2F+F&*,\"#=F+F,F+F-F+F'F+F0F+F&*(\"#F
F+)F0F2F+F1F+F+*(F<F+F0F+F5F+F+F9F'F+F+#F+F6F+*,F2F+F6F&,&*(F6F+F'F+F-
F+F+*$F@F+F&F+F'F&F(#F&F6F&*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF
+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&*(^#F9F+F6F9,&*(F%F&F'F&F(FGF+*,F2F+F6F&FIF
+F'F&F(FLF+F+F+,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&*
(^##F&F2F+F6F9FTF+F+" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 280 111 "Why do you think high school stude
nts are never asked to remember the general formula for the roots of a
 cubic?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 66 "The very idea is depressing. T
his would discourage these students." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "4.  Solving Equations in One Variable.
   There are two different commands to direct Maple to solve an equati
on:  " }{TEXT 285 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 286 7 "fsolve.
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "They have different purposes.  The " 
}{TEXT 287 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 63 " command attempts to find exact sol
utions.  If the expression  " }{TEXT 289 1 "f" }{TEXT -1 116 "  is def
ined in terms of only one variable, there are several different ways t
o direct Maple to solve the equation  " }{TEXT 290 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 
291 4 "0.  " }{TEXT -1 54 "The following all cause Maple to solve the \+
equation   " }{TEXT 292 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 293 2 "0." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 16 "       solve(f);" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f=0);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 20 "      \+
 solve(f=0,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 349 "Maple makes an assumption that if the coefficients of a \+
polynomial are all given exactly (as integers or rational numbers [rat
ios of integer]), then you are only interested in finding exact soluti
ons.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra doesn't guarantee that the so
lutions of  a polynomial can be found exactly, only the polynomial has
 solutions.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 78 "You can force Maple to report additional (approximate) so
lutions by using the " }{TEXT 288 6 "fsolve" }{TEXT -1 188 " command. \+
 (What does the \"f\" stand for?) I think it stands for a approximatio
n that attempts to be as accurate as possiable to a given significasnt
 number.                              In" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
249 "addition, to forcing Maple to report approximate solutions, you c
an specify a field extension (typically real or complex) and require M
aple to look for solutions which fit in that field extension.  Also, o
ne can specify a range of x values and force" }{TEXT 296 7 " fsolve" }
{TEXT -1 75 " to only look for solutions in that specified range.  For
 example, compare:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "fsolve(4*x-x^3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6%$!+++++?!\"*$\"\"!F'$\"+++++?F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "fsolve(4*x-x^3,x=1..4);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+++++?!\"*" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 28 "For each of the polynomials " }{XPPEDIT 
18 0 "p[1]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"\"\"" }{TEXT -1 9 " through " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 
"p[14]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"#9" }{TEXT -1 19 ", do the following:" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "     a.   solve for all exact roots whereever pos
sible, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 59 "     b.   find all approximate
 roots to 10 decimal places, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 43 "     c. \+
 factor each into linear factors.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 106 "You will need to click on  [> in the to
olbar to obtain new execution lines just below the cursor position." }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 
1 "p[1] := x^2-2;" "6#>&%\"pG6#\"\"\",&*$%\"xG\"\"#F'F+!\"\"" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "p[1] := x^2-2;" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"pG6#\"\"\",&*$)%\"xG\"\"#F'F'F,!\"\"" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p[1]);" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$*$\"\"##\"\"\"F$,$F#!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "fsolve(p[1]);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6
$$!+iN@99!\"*$\"+iN@99F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 
"factor(p[1]);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"
\"F(F'!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "factor(p[1],
real);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"$\"+iN@99!\"*
F&F&,&F%F&$\"+iN@99F)!\"\"F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 
1 "p[2] := x^2+2;" "6#>&%\"pG6#\"\"#,&*$%\"xGF'\"\"\"F'F+" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "p[2] := x^2+2;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>&%\"pG6#\"\"#,&*$)%\"xGF'\"\"\"F,F'F," }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p[2]);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6$*&\"\"##\"\"\"F$^#F&F&*&^#!\"\"F&F$F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "fsolve(p[2],x,complex);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
