&%\"xGF($\"+++++]!#5F(F(,&F*F(^#$\"+++++5!\"*F(F(,&F*F(^#$!+++++5F2F(F
(,&F*F($\"+LLLLLF-!\"\"F(,&F*F($F1F2F:F(F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "5.  Solving Systems of Equatio
ns in Several Variables.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 49 "When we have an equation in two variables, e.g.  \+
" }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x -2*y = 5" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%
\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 147 "  we often associate with it a graph,
 the set of points (x,y) in the two-dimensional plane which satisfy th
e equation.  For a linear equation like " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x-2*y = 5
" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 
89 " the graph is a straight line.  For more a complicated equation in
 two variables, e.g.,  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "2*x^3 -3*x + y^2 = x*y" "6#/,
(*&\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"$F'F'*&F*F'F)F'!\"\"*$%\"yGF&F'*&F)F'F.F'" }
{TEXT -1 45 "  the graph becomes a more complicated curve." }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 282 "When we have two
 equations in two variables, we think of the solution set of this syst
em of equations as being the set of points (x,y) which satisfy both eq
uations simultaneously.  In terms of their graphs, the solution set is
 the set of points where the graphs intersect (cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 622 "When we have two \+
linear equations in two variables, since their graphs are straight lin
es, then two straight lines, if they cross, will cross in exactly one \+
place.  Hence, the solution set of the system of equations will be exa
ctly one point (x,y).  If we have two equations which are more complic
ated, then the number of intersection points (crossing points) of thei
r graphs can vary.  For example, if the graph of one equation is a cir
cle and the graph of the other equation is a straight line, then, if t
heir graphs cross, then number of solutions (intersection points) of t
he system of equations could be 1 or 2.  Etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 128 "We can instruct Maple to
 find solutions of systems of equations using the solve or fsolve comm
ands.  The syntax for doing so is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 30 "     solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 85 "where eq
1 and eq2 are equations in the variables x and y.  This is illustrated
 below." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "solve(\{ x + 2*y = 5, 2*x-3*y = -1\},\{x,y\});" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "We could \+
have defined " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 40 "eq1 := x + 2
*y = 5;\neq2 := 2*x-3*y = -1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq
1G/,&%\"xG\"\"\"*&\"\"#F(%\"yGF(F(\"\"&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#>%$eq2G/,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF)F)*&\"\"$F)%\"yGF)!\"\"F." }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 26 "and then \+
given the command" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "solve( \{eq1
,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"
(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 55 "and achieved the same result.  Remember the solution  (" 
}{XPPEDIT 19 1 "13/7" "6#*&\"#8\"\"\"\"\"(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "11/7" "6#*&\"#6\"\"\"\"\"(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 127 ") repre
sents a point in the two-dimensional plane (why two-dimensional?) wher
e the graphs of the equations intersect (cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 63 "Find the solutions, if th
ey exist, for the following equations " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "a.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x - 2*y = 6" "
6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"'" }{TEXT -1 3 ", \+
 " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "4*x + y = -2" "6#/,&*&\"\"%\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'%\"yGF',$
\"\"#!\"\"" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "eq1:=3*x-2*y=6
;\neq2:=4*x+y;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&*&\"\"$\"
\"\"%\"xGF)F)*&\"\"#F)%\"yGF)!\"\"\"\"'" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#>%$eq2G,&*&\"\"%\"\"\"%\"xGF(F(%\"yGF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "solve(\{eq1,eq2\},\{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG#!#C\"#6/%\"xG#\"\"'F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 4 "b.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "6*x -9*y = 12" "6#/,&*&\"\"'\"\"\"%
\"xGF'F'*&\"\"*F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"#7" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3
*y - 2*x = 3" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"yGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"xGF'!\"\"F&" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "eq1:=6*x-9*y=12;\neq2:=3*y-2
*x=3;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&*&\"\"'\"\"\"%\"xGF
)F)*&\"\"*F)%\"yGF)!\"\"\"#7" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq2
G/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"yGF)F)*&\"\"#F)%\"xGF)!\"\"F(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "solve(\{eq1,eq2\},\{x,y\});" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 66 "There was no answer from maple, I'm told \+
these are parallel lines." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "c.  " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "y = x - x^2" "6#/%\"yG,&%\"xG\"\"\"*$F&\"\"#!\"\"" }
{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "y = x-4" "6#/%\"yG,&%\"xG\"\"\"\"\"%!
\"\"" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "eq1:=y=x-x^2;\neq2:=
y=x-4;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/%\"yG,&%\"xG\"\"\"*$
)F(\"\"#F)!\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq2G/%\"yG,&%\"x
G\"\"\"\"\"%!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "solve(
\{eq1,eq2\},\{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$<$/%\"yG!\"#/
%\"xG\"\"#<$/F(F&/F%!\"'" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "d.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "x^2 + y^2 = 16" "6#/
,&*$%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"yGF'F(\"#;" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 
"x^2/36 + y^2/4 = 1" "6#/,&*&%\"xG\"\"#\"#O!\"\"\"\"\"*&%\"yGF'\"\"%F)
F*F*" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 37 "eq1:=x^2+y^2=16;\neq
2:=x^2/36+y^2/4=1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&*$)%\"
xG\"\"#\"\"\"F+*$)%\"yGF*F+F+\"#;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>
%$eq2G/,&*&\"#O!\"\"%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*&\"\"%F)%\"yGF+F,F," }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "solve(\{eq1,eq2\},\{x,y\});" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG-%'RootOfG6#,&\"\"&!\"\"*&\"\"
